n the first season of the HBO series "The White Lotus," it is revealed early on that a character named Armond, played by Murray Bartlett, is dealing with the recent death of a hotel guest. However, it is not revealed until the finale episode who has died.
[Spoiler alert] The person who died in season 1 of "The White Lotus" is revealed to be a character named Tanya McQuoid, played by Jennifer Coolidge. It is revealed that Tanya died of a drug overdose, which Armond had tried to cover up by moving her body to a different room to avoid ruining the hotel's reputation.